<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Aidan O'Brien-trained Derby winner Serpentine has been added to the line-up for Sunday's Qatar Prix de L'Arc de Triomphe after a 72,000 euro supplementary entry fee was paid.</p>

<p>Serpentine was a surprise winner of the Derby at Epsom in July when making all the running and building up an unassailable lead. </p>

<p>He has only run once since when fourth to stablemate Mogul in the Grand Prix de Paris at Longchamp earlier this month when he was ridden with far more restraint.</p>

<p>Serpentine is the only supplementary entry for Sunday's Qatar Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe</p>

<p>Serpentine in a 16-1 shot for the Arc. </p>

<p>He makes up a five-strong challenge for O'Brien - alongside stablemates Love, Magical, Mogul and Sovereign - with 16 entries still in the race.</p>

<p>Final declaration and jockey bookings will be made on Thursday.</p>
